The paper discusses the optimization of multiuser transmit beamforming, which is a common problem in wireless communications and falls under the information theory (cs.IT) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the practical implementation of low-complexity beamforming schemes, which falls under the signal processing (cs.SI) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. Finally, the paper presents a theoretical foundation for the optimal transmit beamforming structure, which falls under the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
